summary:
The Security Council,

Recalling its previous resolutions and Presidential Statements, 

Reaffirming commitment to Syria's sovereignty, independence, unity and territorial integrity, 

Determining the humanitarian situation in Syria threatens peace and security, 

Underscoring Member States' obligation to accept and carry out Council decisions, 

1. Demands full and immediate implementation of all relevant Security Council resolutions; 

2. Renews decisions in paragraphs 2 and 3 of resolution 2165 (2014) for 12 months until 10 July 2021, excluding Al-Ramtha, Al Yarubiyah and Bab al-Salam border crossings; 

3. Requests the Secretary-General to brief the Council monthly and report every 60 days on implementation of resolutions and compliance by all parties in Syria; 

4. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter
